# we are creating here an agent which will tell us about the weather according to cities.
# we are using here pydantic ai as agent framework
# also groq as an LLM model 


# here we are using an AI agent which will use a weather tool for getting the relative answers as per user query.

# the weather tool we created is using openweathermap api docs which is providing all the weather details for specific city.

# the a:\Work\GenAI\AI_Agents\Pydantic_AI\agent.py is the main file were we are creating both the agents and weather tool .


Flow 

User Question
      │
      ▼
weather_agent.run_sync(question)
      │
      ▼
1. Sends the question to the LLM
      │
      ▼
2. LLM reads the system prompt
      │
      ▼
3. LLM decides it needs the
   get_weather_forecast() tool
      │
      ▼
4. PydanticAI calls your Python function
      │
      ▼
5. Function calls OpenWeather API
      │
      ▼
6. Function returns WeatherForecast
      │
      ▼
7. PydanticAI sends the tool result
   back to the LLM
      │
      ▼
8. LLM writes the final answer
      │
      ▼
9. Returns the final result object